---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Learn how SaaSStatsHub publishes structured SaaS research, maintains its open-source frontend, reviews sources, records corrections, and scopes its data.">
  <div class="max-w-[740px] mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6">About SaaSStatsHub</h1>

    <article class="space-y-6 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        <strong class="text-text">SaaSStatsHub</strong> is an early-stage research publishing project
        covering SaaS markets, software categories, product comparisons, and practical buying questions.
        The site combines an Astro frontend with a Headless WordPress publishing workflow and Cloudflare Pages.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-text">Why the Project Exists</h2>
      <p>
        SaaS research is often difficult to evaluate because market estimates use different scopes,
        vendor prices change, and secondary summaries can separate a number from its original context.
        SaaSStatsHub aims to make those boundaries visible by naming sources, dates, methodologies, and
        limitations where they are available.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-text">Who Maintains It</h2>
      <p>
        The project is maintained by a primary independent maintainer under the
        <strong class="text-text">SaaSStatsHub Research Desk</strong> byline. Development, publishing,
        source remediation, deployment, and corrections are managed through the same project workflow.
        The frontend source is available on
        <a href="https://github.com/Kannanyyd/saasstatshub" class="text-primary hover:underline" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-text">How Research Is Handled</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Primary filings, official product documentation, public agencies, and named research reports are preferred.</li>
        <li>Forecasts are distinguished from observed results, and broad cloud totals are not relabeled as SaaS revenue.</li>
        <li>Automated checks help find broken links, duplicate passages, and unsupported claim patterns.</li>
        <li>Pages that cannot meet the current evidence standard may be qualified, rewritten, or moved out of public publication.</li>
        <li>Product pricing and features should be confirmed on the vendor's official site before a buying decision.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Read the complete <a href="/editorial-policy/" class="text-primary hover:underline">Editorial Policy</a>
        for sourcing, corrections, affiliate independence, conflicts, and the use of automated tools.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-text">Open Research Catalog</h2>
      <p>
        The <a href="/research-data/" class="text-primary hover:underline">Research Data page</a> provides
        a machine-readable CSV catalog of currently public articles, including category, canonical URL,
        and last-modified timestamp. It is generated from the publishing system during each production build.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-text">Corrections and Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you find a stale figure, broken source, incorrect scope, or product change, send the article URL,
        the affected passage, and a better primary source through the
        <a href="/contact/" class="text-primary hover:underline">Contact page</a> or email
        <a href="mailto:sangaypopo@gmail.com" class="text-primary hover:underline">sangaypopo@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
